the path to the end

00:15:15.416 --> 00:15:17.090
right from where I'm standing,

00:15:17.114 --> 00:15:18.748
right to the horizon.

00:15:20.041 --> 00:15:21.844
But when you think about it,

00:15:21.868 --> 00:15:25.267
the only environment
in which that would be true

00:15:25.291 --> 00:15:27.734
would be a flat desert,

00:15:28.668 --> 00:15:31.279
empty of any other life.

00:15:32.881 --> 00:15:34.478
But even in a flat desert,

00:15:34.502 --> 00:15:37.780
the curvature of the earth
would take the path away from you.

00:15:38.584 --> 00:15:40.138
So, no;

00:15:40.162 --> 00:15:41.777
you see the path,

00:15:41.801 --> 00:15:43.683
and then you don't

00:15:43.707 --> 00:15:45.642
and then you see it again.

00:15:45.666 --> 00:15:47.786
So this is "Santiago,"

00:15:48.688 --> 00:15:50.597
the supposed arrival,

00:15:51.225 --> 00:15:54.980
which is a kind of return
to the beginning all at the same time.

00:15:55.608 --> 00:15:57.954
We have this experience of the journey,

00:15:57.978 --> 00:16:00.684
which is in all of our great
spiritual traditions,

00:16:00.708 --> 00:16:01.861
of pilgrimage.

00:16:01.885 --> 00:16:06.155
But just by actually standing
in the ground of your life fully,

00:16:06.179 --> 00:16:10.269
not trying to abstract yourself
into a strategic future

00:16:10.293 --> 00:16:13.950
that's actually just an escape
from present heartbreak;

00:16:13.974 --> 00:16:16.783
the ability to stand
in the ground of your life

00:16:16.807 --> 00:16:20.196
and to look at the horizon
that is pulling you --

00:16:20.220 --> 00:16:21.538
in that moment,

00:16:21.562 --> 00:16:23.040
you are the whole journey.

00:16:23.064 --> 00:16:25.419
You are the whole conversation.

